  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bring Quality Education to 50MM Brazilian Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Brazil has placed almost every children and youth at school, but it still does not guarantee learning: in the Pisa exam ranking, Brazil occupies the 66th position out of 70. Todos Pela Educacao (All For Education), a main Brazilian NGOs, aims to improve Brazil, by boosting the quality and equity of Basic Education. Via advocacy and public monitoring, the goal is to make a qualitative leap in Brazilian K12 Education so that the 48.6 million Brazilian students have better opportunities for life.</narrative>
  </description>
